PROJECT-WIDE APPROVED TERMINOLOGY (MANDATORY — APPLY IN ADDITION TO %TERMS%):
The following EN→TR mappings are binding for the entire Uster AFIS 6 / textile-machinery domain. They override any MT default. If the source contains the English term (in any inflection or casing), the Turkish target MUST use the exact base form below, with only Turkish inflectional suffixes appended where grammar requires.

Combing / Carding distinction (CRITICAL — frequently confused by MT):
- comber → penye makinesi
- comber sliver → penye şeridi
- comber lap → penye vatkası
- comber noil → penye telefi
- combing (process) → tarama
- combed (adjective, e.g. "combed cotton") → penye  (NEVER "taraklı")
- noil → telef

- card (machine) → tarak  (NEVER "kart")
- cards → taraklar
- card mat → tarak tülbendi  ("tülbent" is reserved for card only)
- card sliver → tarak şeridi
- carded (adjective, e.g. "carded cotton") → karde
- carded sliver → karde şerit
- carding (process) → taraklama
- card clothing → tarak garnitürleri  (NEVER "tarak giydirmesi")

Other binding mappings:
- trash → çepel  (NEVER "çöpel")
- trash removal → çepel uzaklaştırma
- nep removal → nep uzaklaştırma
- spinning mill → iplik fabrikası  (preferred; "iplikhane" acceptable but discouraged)
- lap → vatka
- raw material → ham madde  (TDK: WRITTEN AS TWO SEPARATE WORDS; "hammadde" is INCORRECT — applies to all inflected forms: "ham maddesi", "ham maddenin", "ham maddeyi", etc.)
- virgin (textile context, e.g. "Polyester, virgin" / "Virgin Polyester") → işlenmemiş  (NEVER "ham", NEVER "bakir")
- draw frame sliver → cer makinesi şeridi
- sliver evenness → şerit düzgünlüğü
- fiber → elyaf  (NEVER "lif")
- fiber length / staple length → stapel uzunluğu  (NEVER "lif uzunluğu")
- roving → fitil
- man-made fiber / synthetic fiber → sentetik elyaf  (NEVER "insan yapımı elyaf")
- blow room → harman hallaç odası
- benchmark → benchmark  (DO NOT TRANSLATE — keep as-is)

